State of Connecticut v. William Outlaw (9147)

O’Connell, Landau and Heiman, Js.

Argued February 7 decision released March 5, 1991 Patrick J. Culligan, assistant public defender, for the appellant (defendant). Carolyn K. Longstreth, assistant state’s attorney, with whom were Elpedio N. Vitale, assistant state’s attorney, and, on the brief, Michael Dearington, state’s attorney, for the appellee (state). Per Curiam.

The judgment is affirmed.
